{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775862752928,"sessionID":"ses_286553ee8ffe1yJNKlcIkTBKVm","part":{"id":"prt_d79ab208800122Fd3JfKiAcVkm","messageID":"msg_d79ab0f11001LoLCepwU1jrYaL","sessionID":"ses_286553ee8ffe1yJNKlcIkTBKVm","type":"tool","tool":"grep","callID":"toolu_111571a9cb2f4fd695e04c29","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"path":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z","pattern":"AR-018|Agentd.*空闲|idle.*cleanup"},"output":"Found 25 matches\n/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/.sdd_prompt.md:\n  Line 3: AR: AR-018 — Agentd 空闲清理控制器\n\n/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/changes/AR-018/proposal.md:\n  Line 1: # Proposal: Agentd Idle Cleanup Controller (AR-018)\n  Line 5: Implement an idle cleanup controller in `pkg/agentd` that automatically identifies and terminates idle AgentRuntime and CodeInterpreter resources based on configurable inactivity timeouts, releasing cluster resources and maintaining system hygiene.\n  Line 27: - `pkg/agentd/idle_cleanup.go` - Idle cleanup controller interface and implementation\n  Line 30: - `pkg/agentd/config.go` - Configuration for idle timeouts and cleanup behavior\n  Line 31: - `pkg/agentd/idle_cleanup_test.go` - Unit tests for cleanup logic\n  Line 160:     // Start starts the idle cleanup controller\n  Line 227:     // Enabled enables the idle cleanup controller\n  Line 351:     c.logger.Info(\"Starting idle cleanup controller\",\n  Line 426: func (c *idleCleanupController) cleanupResource(ctx context.Context, kind, namespace, name string) error {\n  Line 573: | `AGENTD_CLEANUP_ENABLED` | No | `true` | Enable/disable idle cleanup |\n\n/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/changes/AR-018/README.md:\n  Line 1: # AR-018: Agentd 空闲清理控制器\n\n/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/openc