{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775862757906,"sessionID":"ses_286553ee8ffe1yJNKlcIkTBKVm","part":{"id":"prt_d79ab352f001z3Iu720OYnUecS","messageID":"msg_d79ab26db001gid2A19iGQ8fPe","sessionID":"ses_286553ee8ffe1yJNKlcIkTBKVm","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_841ae708a5d3488589d65291","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/idle-cleanup/design.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/idle-cleanup/design.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # Idle Cleanup — Design\n2: \n3: ## Module\n4: \n5: - `github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube` (see root `go.mod` in sandbox-orchestration design).\n6: \n7: ## Package `github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/pkg/agentd`\n8: \n9: ### Time threshold\n10: \n11: ```go\n12: var SessionExpirationTimeout = 15 * time.Minute\n13: ```\n14: \n15: Idle expiration: `expirationTime := lastActivity.Add(SessionExpirationTimeout)`; delete when `time.Now().After(expirationTime)`.\n16: \n17: ### Annotation key\n18: \n19: The reconciler uses the same key as workload manager pod annotation for idle timeout tracking on the **Sandbox** object:\n20: \n21: - Import: `github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/pkg/workloadmanager`\n22: - Key: `workloadmanager.LastActivityAnnotationKey` = **`\"last-activity-time\"`**\n23: \n24: (Workload manager also sets `runtime.agentcube.io/idle-timeout` on Sandbox metadata for template-driven idle configuration; **agentd** only reads `last-activity-time`.)\n25: \n26: ### Reconciler\n27: \n28: ```go\n29: package agentd\n30: \n31: type Reconciler struct {\n32:     client.Client\n33:     Scheme *runtime.Scheme\n34: }\n35: \n36: func (r *Reconciler) Reconcile(ctx context.Context, req ctrl.Request) (ctrl.Result, error)\n37: ```\n38: \n39: **Algorithm (exact behavior):**\n40: \n41: 1. `sandbox := &sandboxv1alpha1.Sandbox{}`; `Get(ctx, req.NamespacedName, sandbox)`.\n42: 2. If `errors.IsNotFound(err)` → `return ctrl.Result{}, nil`.\n43: 3. If other get error → return `ctrl.Result{}, err`.\n44: 4. `lastActivityStr, exists := sandbox.Annotations[workloadmanager.LastActivityAnnotationKey]`.\n45: 5. If `exists && lastActivityStr != \"\"`:\n46:    - `lastActivity, err := time.Parse(time.RFC3339, lastActivityStr)`\n47:    - If parse err → `return ctrl.Result{RequeueAfter: 30 * time.Second}, err`\n48:    - `expirationTime := lastActivity.Add(SessionExpirationTimeout)`\n49:    - If `time.Now().After(expirationTime)`:\n50:      - `r.Delete(ctx, sandbox)`; if err and not `IsNotFound` → `return ctrl.Result{}, err`\n51:    - Else:\n52:      - `return ctrl.Result{RequeueAfter: time.Until(expirationTime)}, nil`\n53: 6. `return ctrl.Result{}, nil`\n54: \n55: ### SetupWithManager\n56: \n57: ```go\n58: func (r *Reconciler) SetupWithManager(mgr ctrl.Manager) error {\n59:     return ctrl.NewControllerManagedBy(mgr).\n60:         For(&sandboxv1alpha1.Sandbox{}).\n61:         Complete(r)\n62: }\n63: ```\n64: \n65: ## Binary `cmd/agentd/main.go`\n66: \n67: ### Scheme registration\n68: \n69: ```go\n70: var schemeBuilder = runtime.NewScheme()\n71: \n72: func init() {\n73:     utilruntime.Must(scheme.AddToScheme(schemeBuilder))\n74:     utilruntime.Must(sandboxv1alpha1.AddToScheme(schemeBuilder))\n75: }\n76: ```\n77: \n78: ### Controller-runtime manager\n79: \n80: ```go\n81: mgr, err := ctrl.NewManager(ctrl.GetConfigOrDie(), ctrl.Options{\n82:     Scheme:                 schemeBuilder,\n83:     Metrics:                metricsserver.Options{BindAddress: \"0\"},\n84:     HealthProbeBindAddress:   \"0\",\n85: })\n86: ```\n87: \n88: ### Controller registration (duplicate of SetupWithManager pattern)\n89: \n90: ```go\n91: err = ctrl.NewControllerManagedBy(mgr).\n92:     For(&sandboxv1alpha1.Sandbox{}).\n93:     Complete(&agentd.Reconciler{\n94:         Client: mgr.GetClient(),\n95:         Scheme: mgr.GetScheme(),\n96:     })\n97: ```\n98: \n99: ### Run\n100: \n101: ```go\n102: mgr.Start(ctrl.SetupSignalHandler())\n103: ```\n104: \n105: ## Watched resources\n106: \n107: | API group | Version | Kind | Trigger |\n108: |-----------|---------|------|---------|\n109: | `agents.x-k8s.io` | `v1alpha1` | `Sandbox` | Default `For()` watch — creates, updates, deletes (per controller-runtime) |\n110: \n111: No explicit `Owns` or `Watches` — single primary resource `Sandbox`.\n112: \n113: ## Related workload-manager constants (context)\n114: \n115: From `pkg/workloadmanager` (not used by agentd reconcile logic but set when sandboxes are created):\n116: \n117: - `IdleTimeoutAnnotationKey = \"runtime.agentcube.io/idle-timeout\"` — duration string on Sandbox CR.\n118: - `LastActivityAnnotationKey = \"last-activity-time\"` — **read by agentd** for idle cleanup.\n119: \n120: ## Dependencies\n121: \n122: - `k8s.io/apimachinery/pkg/api/errors`\n123: - `k8s.io/apimachinery/pkg/runtime`\n124: - `sigs.k8s.io/agent-sandbox/api/v1alpha1`\n125: - `sigs.k8s.io/controller-runtime`\n126: - `github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/pkg/workloadmanager` (annotation key only)\n\n(End of file - total 126 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# Idle Cleanup — Design\n\n## Module\n\n- `github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube` (see root `go.mod` in sandbox-orchestration design).\n\n## Package `github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/pkg/agentd`\n\n### Time threshold\n\n```go\nvar SessionExpirationTimeout = 15 * time.Minute\n```\n\nIdle expiration: `expirationTime := lastActivity.Add(SessionExpirationTimeout)`; delete when `time.Now().After(expirationTime)`.\n\n### Annotation key\n\nThe reconciler uses the same key as workload manager pod annotation for idle timeout tracking on the **Sandbox** object:\n","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/idle-cleanup/design.md","time":{"start":1775862757891,"end":1775862757904}}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775862757923,"sessionID":"ses_286553ee8ffe1yJNKlcIkTBKVm","part":{"id":"prt_d79ab2fb9001hhCzsNBOfppQBy","messageID":"msg_d79ab26db001gid2A19iGQ8fPe","sessionID":"ses_286553ee8ffe1yJNKlcIkTBKVm","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_0ca38ed3ed614690bd338c40","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/changes/AR-018/proposal.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/changes/AR-018/proposal.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # Proposal: Agentd Idle Cleanup Controller (AR-018)\n2: \n3: ## Summary\n4: \n5: Implement an idle cleanup controller in `pkg/agentd` that automatically identifies and terminates idle AgentRuntime and CodeInterpreter resources based on configurable inactivity timeouts, releasing cluster resources and maintaining system hygiene.\n6: \n7: ---\n8: \n9: ## Purpose\n10: \n11: The Agentd Idle Cleanup Controller provides:\n12: \n13: 1. **Resource Reclamation**: Automatically clean up idle agent runtimes and code interpreters to free cluster resources\n14: 2. **Configurable Idle Detection**: Support per-resource-type idle timeout configuration\n15: 3. **Graceful Termination**: Properly finalize resources before deletion with status updates\n16: 4. **Observability**: Emit metrics and logs for cleanup operations\n17: 5. **Safe Operation**: Respect resource11s and avoid cleaning resources with active workloads\n18: \n19: This implementation builds upon the client-go infrastructure from `deployment/client-go.md` and integrates with the workload manager's reconciliation loop to ensure cleaned resources are properly handled.\n20: \n21: ---\n22: \n23: ## Scope\n24: \n25: ### In Scope\n26: \n27: - `pkg/agentd/idle_cleanup.go` - Idle cleanup controller interface and implementation\n28: - `pkg/agentd/idle_tracker.go` - Idle state tracking and timeout detection\n29: - `pkg/agentd/cleanup_metrics.go` - Metrics for cleanup operations\n30: - `pkg/agentd/config.go` - Configuration for idle timeouts and cleanup behavior\n31: - `pkg/agentd/idle_cleanup_test.go` - Unit tests for cleanup logic\n32: - `pkg/agentd/idle_tracker_test.go` - Unit tests for idle detection\n33: - `pkg/agentd/integration_test.go` - Integration tests with fake clients\n34: \n35: ### Out of Scope\n36: \n37: - Manual termination APIs (covered by workload manager handlers)\n38: - Resource scaling policies (future AR)\n39: - Cross-namespace cleanup coordination\n40: - Custom resource definition modifications\n41: - User notification systems for impending cleanup\n42: \n43: ---\n44: \n45: ## Impact Analysis\n46: \n47: ### Dependencies\n48: \n49: | Package | Purpose |\n50: |---------|---------|\n51: | `k8s.io/client-go/kubernetes` | Kubernetes client interface |\n52: | `k8s.io/apimachinery/pkg/apis/meta/v1` | Metadata and deletion options |\n53: | `k8s.io/apimachinery/pkg/watch` | Watch interface for resource monitoring |\n54: | `github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/client-go` | Generated client for runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh |\n55: | `github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1` | AgentRuntime and CodeInterpreter types |\n56: | `k8s.io/klog/v2` | Structured logging |\n57: | `prometheus/client_golang/prometheus` | Metrics exposition |\n58: | `golang.org/x/sync/errgroup` | Concurrent cleanup operations |\n59: \n60: ### Affected Components\n61: \n62: 1. **Workload Manager**: Receives deletion events for cleaned resources; must handle graceful termination\n63: 2. **Reconciler**: Processes status updates from cleanup operations; updates finalizers\n64: 3. **Metrics System**: Exposes cleanup metrics for monitoring dashboards\n65: 4. **Router Session Manager**: May need to invalidate sessions for cleaned resources\n66: \n67: ### Backward Compatibility\n68: \n69: - This is a new controller within agentd\n70: - No breaking changes to existing APIs\n71: - Configuration via environment variables with sensible defaults\n72: - Can be disabled via configuration flag\n73: \n74: ### Risk Assessment\n75: \n76: | Risk | Likelihood | Impact | Mitigation |\n77: |------|------------|--------|------------|\n78: | Premature cleanup of active resources | Low | High | Conservative idle detection, last-activity tracking from workload manager |\n79: | Cleanup storm under load | Medium | Medium | Rate limiting, concurrent cleanup limits |\n80: | Resource leak if cleanup fails | Medium | Medium | Retry logic, metrics for failed cleanups |\n81: | Watch connection failures | Medium | Low | Exponential backoff, periodic full scans |\n82: | Namespace isolation violations | Low | High | Namespace-scoped clients, validation |\n83: \n84: ---\n85: \n86: ## Alternatives Considered\n87: \n88: ### Alternative 1: TTL-Based Kubernetes Finalizers\n89: \n90: **Approach**: Use Kubernetes native TTL secondsAfterFinished on resources\n91: \n92: **Pros**:\n93: - Leverages Kubernetes garbage collection\n94: - No additional controller logic needed\n95: - Native integration with Kubernetes lifecycle\n96: \n97: **Cons**:\n98: - Requires CRD modifications\n99: - Only triggers after completion, not for idle resources\n100: - Less flexible timeout configuration\n101: \n102: **Decision**: Implement custom idle detection for more granular control.\n103: \n104: ### Alternative 2: Workload Manager Integrated Cleanup\n105: \n106: **Approach**: Add cleanup logic directly to workload manager reconciliation loop\n107: \n108: **Pros**:\n109: - Single reconciliation loop\n110: - Direct access to workload state\n111: - No inter-controller coordination\n112: \n113: **Cons**:\n114: - Bloated reconciliation logic\n115: - Cleanup delays during high reconciliation load\n116: - Harder to tune cleanup independently\n117: \n118: **Decision**: Separate controller for cleaner separation of concerns and independent tuning.\n119: \n120: ### Alternative 3: CronJob-Based Cleanup\n121: \n122: **Approach**: Deploy cleanup logic as periodic Kubernetes CronJob\n123: \n124: **Pros**:\n125: - Simple to understand and deploy\n126: - Kubernetes-native scheduling\n127: - No long-running process\n128: \n129: **Cons**:\n130: - No real-time idle detection\n131: - Potential race conditions with concurrent runs\n132: - Less responsive to load changes\n133: \n134: **Decision**: Continuous controller for better responsiveness and state tracking.\n135: \n136: ### Alternative 4: Label-Based Selection\n137: \n138: **Approach**: Use label selectors to mark resources for cleanup, separate finalizer processes them\n139: \n140: **Pros**:\n141: - Clear separation of detection and execution\n142: - Audit trail via labels\n143: - Easier debugging\n144: \n145: **Cons**:\n146: - Additional API surface (label management)\n147: - More complex state machine\n148: - Label cleanup required\n149: \n150: **Decision**: Direct deletion for simpler implementation; can add labels later for audit.\n151: \n152: ---\n153: \n154: ## Implementation Details\n155: \n156: ### IdleCleanupController Interface\n157: \n158: ```go\n159: type IdleCleanupController interface {\n160:     // Start starts the idle cleanup controller\n161:     Start(ctx context.Context) error\n162:     \n163:     // Stop stops the controller gracefully\n164:     Stop()\n165:     \n166:     // CleanupNow triggers an immediate cleanup cycle\n167:     CleanupNow(ctx context.Context) (CleanupResult, error)\n168: }\n169: \n170: type CleanupResult struct {\n171:     AgentRuntimesCleaned   int\n172:     CodeInterpretersCleaned int\n173:     Errors                 []CleanupError\n174: }\n175: \n176: type CleanupError struct {\n177:     ResourceKind string\n178:     Name         string\n179:     Namespace    string\n180:     Error        error\n181: }\n182: ```\n183: \n184: ### IdleTracker Interface\n185: \n186: ```go\n187: type IdleTracker interface {\n188:     // UpdateLastActivity updates the last activity timestamp for a resource\n189:     UpdateLastActivity(kind, namespace, name string, timestamp time.Time)\n190:     \n191:     // GetLastActivity retrieves the last activity timestamp\n192:     GetLastActivity(kind, namespace, name string) (time.Time, bool)\n193:     \n194:     // IsIdle checks if a resource is idle based on current time\n195:     IsIdle(kind, namespace, name string, timeout time.Duration) bool\n196:     \n197:     // Remove removes a resource from tracking\n198:     Remove(kind, namespace, name string)\n199:     \n200:     // ListIdleResources returns all idle resources exceeding timeout\n201:     ListIdleResources(timeout time.Duration) []ResourceKey\n202: }\n203: \n204: type ResourceKey struct {\n205:     Kind      string\n206:     Namespace string\n207:     Name      string\n208: }\n209: ```\n210: \n211: ### Configuration\n212: \n213: ```go\n214: type CleanupConfig struct {\n215:     // AgentRuntimeIdleTimeout is the idle timeout for AgentRuntimes\n216:     AgentRuntimeIdleTimeout time.Duration\n217:     \n218:     // CodeInterpreterIdleTimeout is the idle timeout for CodeInterpreters\n219:     CodeInterpreterIdleTimeout time.Duration\n220:     \n221:     // CleanupInterval is how often to run cleanup cycles\n222:     CleanupInterval time.Duration\n223:     \n224:     // MaxConcurrentCleanups limits concurrent deletion operations\n225:     MaxConcurrentCleanups int\n226:     \n227:     // Enabled enables the idle cleanup controller\n228:     Enabled bool\n229:     \n230:     // DryRun enables dry-run mode (log only, no deletions)\n231:     DryRun bool\n232:     \n233:     // NamespaceAllowList restricts cleanup to specific namespaces (empty = all)\n234:     NamespaceAllowList []string\n235:     \n236:     // NamespaceDenyList excludes specific namespaces from cleanup\n237:     NamespaceDenyList []string\n238: }\n239: \n240: func DefaultCleanupConfig() *CleanupConfig {\n241:     return &CleanupConfig{\n242:         AgentRuntimeIdleTimeout:    30 * time.Minute,\n243:         CodeInterpreterIdleTimeout: 15 * time.Minute,\n244:         CleanupInterval:           5 * time.Minute,\n245:         MaxConcurrentCleanups:     10,\n246:         Enabled:                   true,\n247:         DryRun:                    false,\n248:     }\n249: }\n250: ```\n251: \n252: ### Metrics\n253: \n254: ```go\n255: type CleanupMetrics struct {\n256:     // agentRuntimeCleanupsTotal counts total AgentRuntime cleanups\n257:     agentRuntimeCleanupsTotal prometheus.Counter\n258:     \n259:     // codeInterpreterCleanupsTotal counts total CodeInterpreter cleanups\n260:     codeInterpreterCleanupsTotal prometheus.Counter\n261:     \n262:     // cleanupErrorsTotal counts cleanup errors by kind\n263:     cleanupErrorsTotal *prometheus.CounterVec\n264:     \n265:     // cleanupDurationSeconds tracks cleanup operation duration\n266:     cleanupDurationSeconds *prometheus.HistogramVec\n267:     \n268:     // idleResourcesDetected tracks detected idle resources\n269:     idleResourcesDetected *prometheus.GaugeVec\n270: }\n271: \n272: func (m *CleanupMetrics) RecordCleanup(kind string, duration time.Duration, err error)\n273: func (m *CleanupMetrics) SetIdleCount(kind string, count int)\n274: func (m *CleanupMetrics) RecordError(kind string)\n275: ```\n276: \n277: ### Idle Detection Logic\n278: \n279: ```go\n280: type idleTracker struct {\n281:     mu           sync.RWMutex\n282:     lastActivity map[ResourceKey]time.Time\n283:     logger       klog.Logger\n284: }\n285: \n286: func (t *idleTracker) UpdateLastActivity(kind, namespace, name string, timestamp time.Time) {\n287:     t.mu.Lock()\n288:     defer t.mu.Unlock()\n289:     \n290:     key := ResourceKey{Kind: kind, Namespace: namespace, Name: name}\n291:     t.lastActivity[key] = timestamp\n292:     \n293:     t.logger.V(4).Info(\"Updated last activity\",\n294:         \"kind\", kind,\n295:         \"namespace\", namespace,\n296:         \"name\", name,\n297:         \"timestamp\", timestamp)\n298: }\n299: \n300: func (t *idleTracker) IsIdle(kind, namespace, name string, timeout time.Duration) bool {\n301:     t.mu.RLock()\n302:     defer t.mu.RUnlock()\n303:     \n304:     key := ResourceKey{Kind: kind, Namespace: namespace, Name: name}\n305:     lastActivity, exists := t.lastActivity[key]\n306:     \n307:     if !exists {\n308:         // No activity recorded; use creation time as fallback\n309:         return true\n310:     }\n311:     \n312:     return time.Since(lastActivity) >= timeout\n313: }\n314: \n315: func (t *idleTracker) ListIdleResources(timeout time.Duration) []ResourceKey {\n316:     t.mu.RLock()\n317:     defer t.mu.RUnlock()\n318:     \n319:     now := time.Now()\n320:     var idle []ResourceKey\n321:     \n322:     for key, lastActivity := range t.lastActivity {\n323:         if now.Sub(lastActivity) >= timeout {\n324:             idle = append(idle, key)\n325:         }\n326:     }\n327:     \n328:     return idle\n329: }\n330: ```\n331: \n332: ### Cleanup Controller Implementation\n333: \n334: ```go\n335: type idleCleanupController struct {\n336:     config       *CleanupConfig\n337:     agentClient  versioned.Interface\n338:     idleTracker  IdleTracker\n339:     metrics      *CleanupMetrics\n340:     logger       klog.Logger\n341:     stopCh       chan struct{}\n342:     wg           sync.WaitGroup\n343: }\n344: \n345: func (c *idleCleanupController) Start(ctx context.Context) error {\n346:     if !c.config.Enabled {\n347:         c.logger.Info(\"Idle cleanup controller is disabled\")\n348:         return nil\n349:     }\n350:     \n351:     c.logger.Info(\"Starting idle cleanup controller\",\n352:         \"agentRuntimeTimeout\", c.config.AgentRuntimeIdleTimeout,\n353:         \"codeInterpreterTimeout\", c.config.CodeInterpreterIdleTimeout,\n354:         \"cleanupInterval\", c.config.CleanupInterval)\n355:     \n356:     // Start watch for resource status updates\n357:     c.wg.Add(1)\n358:     go func() {\n359:         defer c.wg.Done()\n360:         c.watchResources(ctx)\n361:     }()\n362:     \n363:     // Start periodic cleanup\n364:     c.wg.Add(1)\n365:     go func() {\n366:         defer c.wg.Done()\n367:         ticker := time.NewTicker(c.config.CleanupInterval)\n368:         defer ticker.Stop()\n369:         \n370:         for {\n371:             select {\n372:             case <-ctx.Done():\n373:                 return\n374:             case <-c.stopCh:\n375:                 return\n376:             case <-ticker.C:\n377:                 c.runCleanup(ctx)\n378:             }\n379:         }\n380:     }()\n381:     \n382:     return nil\n383: }\n384: \n385: func (c *idleCleanupController) runCleanup(ctx context.Context) {\n386:     c.logger.V(4).Info(\"Starting cleanup cycle\")\n387:     \n388:     var g errgroup.Group\n389:     g.SetLimit(c.config.MaxConcurrentCleanups)\n390:     \n391:     // Clean idle AgentRuntimes\n392:     agentIdle := c.idleTracker.ListIdleResources(c.config.AgentRuntimeIdleTimeout)\n393:     c.metrics.SetIdleCount(\"AgentRuntime\", len(agentIdle))\n394:     \n395:     for _, key := range agentIdle {\n396:         if !c.isNamespaceAllowed(key.Namespace) {\n397:             continue\n398:         }\n399:         \n400:         g.Go(func() error {\n401:             return c.cleanupResource(ctx, key.Kind, key.Namespace, key.Name)\n402:         })\n403:     }\n404:     \n405:     // Clean idle CodeInterpreters\n406:     ciIdle := c.idleTracker.ListIdleResources(c.config.CodeInterpreterIdleTimeout)\n407:     c.metrics.SetIdleCount(\"CodeInterpreter\", len(ciIdle))\n408:     \n409:     for _, key := range ciIdle {\n410:         if !c.isNamespaceAllowed(key.Namespace) {\n411:             continue\n412:         }\n413:         \n414:         g.Go(func() error {\n415:             return c.cleanupResource(ctx, key.Kind, key.Namespace, key.Name)\n416:         })\n417:     }\n418:     \n419:     if err := g.Wait(); err != nil {\n420:         c.logger.Error(err, \"Cleanup cycle completed with errors\")\n421:     } else {\n422:         c.logger.V(4).Info(\"Cleanup cycle completed successfully\")\n423:     }\n424: }\n425: \n426: func (c *idleCleanupController) cleanupResource(ctx context.Context, kind, namespace, name string) error {\n427:     start := time.Now()\n428:     var err error\n429:     \n430:     if c.config.DryRun {\n431:         c.logger.Info(\"[DRY RUN] Would clean idle resource\",\n432:             \"kind\", kind,\n433:             \"namespace\", namespace,\n434:             \"name\", name)\n435:         c.metrics.RecordCleanup(kind, time.Since(start), nil)\n436:         return nil\n437:     }\n438:     \n439:     switch kind {\n440:     case \"AgentRuntime\":\n441:         err = c.agentClient.RuntimeV1alpha1().AgentRuntimes(namespace).Delete(\n442:             ctx, name, metav1.DeleteOptions{\n443:                 GracePeriodSeconds: ptr.To(int64(30)),\n444:                 PropagationPolicy:  ptr.To(metav1.DeletePropagationForeground),\n445:             })\n446:     case \"CodeInterpreter\":\n447:         err = c.agentClient.RuntimeV1alpha1().CodeInterpreters(namespace).Delete(\n448:             ctx, name, metav1.DeleteOptions{\n449:                 GracePeriodSeconds: ptr.To(int64(30)),\n450:                 PropagationPolicy:  ptr.To(metav1.DeletePropagationForeground),\n451:             })\n452:     default:\n453:         err = fmt.Errorf(\"unknown resource kind: %s\", kind)\n454:     }\n455:     \n456:     c.metrics.RecordCleanup(kind, time.Since(start), err)\n457:     \n458:     if err != nil {\n459:         c.logger.Error(err, \"Failed to cleanup idle resource\",\n460:             \"kind\", kind,\n461:             \"namespace\", namespace,\n462:             \"name\", name)\n463:         return err\n464:     }\n465:     \n466:     c.logger.Info(\"Cleaned up idle resource\",\n467:         \"kind\", kind,\n468:         \"namespace\", namespace,\n469:         \"name\", name)\n470:     \n471:     // Remove from idle tracker\n472:     c.idleTracker.Remove(kind, namespace, name)\n473:     \n474:     return nil\n475: }\n476: \n477: func (c *idleCleanupController) watchResources(ctx context.Context) {\n478:     // Watch AgentRuntimes\n479:     go c.watchAgentRuntimes(ctx)\n480:     \n481:     // Watch CodeInterpreters\n482:     go c.watchCodeInterpreters(ctx)\n483:     \n484:     <-ctx.Done()\n485: }\n486: \n487: func (c *idleCleanupController) watchAgentRuntimes(ctx context.Context) {\n488:     watcher, err := c.agentClient.RuntimeV1alpha1().AgentRuntimes(metav1.NamespaceAll).Watch(\n489:         ctx, metav1.ListOptions{\n490:             TimeoutSeconds: ptr.To(int64(300)),\n491:         })\n492:     if err != nil {\n493:         c.logger.Error(err, \"Failed to watch AgentRuntimes\")\n494:         return\n495:     }\n496:     \n497:     for {\n498:         select {\n499:         case <-ctx.Done():\n500:             watcher.Stop()\n501:             return\n502:         case event, ok := <-watcher.ResultChan():\n503:             if !ok {\n504:                 return\n505:             }\n506:             \n507:             ar, ok := event.Object.(*runtimev1alpha1.AgentRuntime)\n508:             if !ok {\n509:                 continue\n510:             }\n511:             \n512:             key := ResourceKey{\n513:                 Kind:      \"AgentRuntime\",\n514:                 Namespace: ar.Namespace,\n515:                 Name:      ar.Name,\n516:             }\n517:             \n518:             switch event.Type {\n519:             case watch.Added, watch.Modified:\n520:                 // Update last activity from status.lastActivity or metadata.creationTimestamp\n521:                 c.updateResourceActivity(key, ar.Status.LastActivityTime, ar.CreationTimestamp)\n522:             case watch.Deleted:\n523:                 c.idleTracker.Remove(key.Kind, key.Namespace, key.Name)\n524:             }\n525:         }\n526:     }\n527: }\n528: \n529: func (c *idleCleanupController) watchCodeInterpreters(ctx context.Context) {\n530:     // Similar to watchAgentRuntimes but for CodeInterpreters\n531:     // ... implementation ...\n532: }\n533: \n534: func (c *idleCleanupController) updateResourceActivity(key ResourceKey, lastActivity, creation metav1.Time) {\n535:     if !lastActivity.IsZero() {\n536:         c.idleTracker.UpdateLastActivity(key.Kind, key.Namespace, key.Name, lastActivity.Time)\n537:     } else {\n538:         c.idleTracker.UpdateLastActivity(key.Kind, key.Namespace, key.Name, creation.Time)\n539:     }\n540: }\n541: \n542: func (c *idleCleanupController) isNamespaceAllowed(namespace string) bool {\n543:     // Check deny list first\n544:     for _, denied := range c.config.NamespaceDenyList {\n545:         if namespace == denied {\n546:             return false\n547:         }\n548:     }\n549:     \n550:     // Check allow list\n551:     if len(c.config.NamespaceAllowList) == 0 {\n552:         return true\n553:     }\n554:     \n555:     for _, allowed := range c.config.NamespaceAllowList {\n556:         if namespace == allowed {\n557:             return true\n558:         }\n559:     }\n560:     \n561:     return false\n562: }\n563: ```\n564: \n565: ---\n566: \n567: ## Configuration Reference\n568: \n569: ### Environment Variables\n570: \n571: | Variable | Required | Default | Notes |\n572: |----------|----------|---------|-------|\n573: | `AGENTD_CLEANUP_ENABLED` | No | `true` | Enable/disable idle cleanup |\n574: | `AGENTD_CLEANUP_DRY_RUN` | No | `false` | Log only, no deletions |\n575: | `AGENTD_AGENT_RUNTIME_IDLE_TIMEOUT` | No | `30m` | AgentRuntime idle timeout |\n576: | `AGENTD_CODE_INTERPRETER_IDLE_TIMEOUT` | No | `15m` | CodeInterpreter idle timeout |\n577: | `AGENTD_CLEANUP_INTERVAL` | No | `5m` | Cleanup cycle interval |\n578: | `AGENTD_MAX_CONCURRENT_CLEANUPS` | No | `10` | Max concurrent deletions |\n579: | `AGENTD_CLEANUP_NAMESPACE_ALLOW_LIST` | No | `` | Comma-separated allowed namespaces |\n580: | `AGENTD_CLEANUP_NAMESPACE_DENY_LIST` | No | `kube-system,kube-public` | Comma-separated excluded namespaces |\n581: \n582: ### Example Configuration\n583: \n584: ```go\n585: config := &CleanupConfig{\n586:     AgentRuntimeIdleTimeout:    30 * time.Minute,\n587:     CodeInterpreterIdleTimeout: 15 * time.Minute,\n588:     CleanupInterval:           5 * time.Minute,\n589:     MaxConcurrentCleanups:     10,\n590:     Enabled:                   true,\n591:     DryRun:                    false,\n592:     NamespaceAllowList:        []string{\"default\", \"agent-workloads\"},\n593:     NamespaceDenyList:         []string{\"kube-system\", \"kube-public\", \"monitoring\"},\n594: }\n595: ```\n596: \n597: ---\n598: \n599: ## Testing Strategy\n600: \n601: ### Unit Tests\n602: \n603: | Test | Purpose |\n604: |------|---------|\n605: | `TestIdleTracker_UpdateLastActivity` | Verify activity timestamp updates |\n606: | `TestIdleTracker_IsIdle` | Test idle detection logic |\n607: | `TestIdleTracker_ListIdleResources` | Test listing idle resources |\n608: | `TestIdleTracker_Remove` | Test resource removal from tracking |\n609: | `TestCleanupController_runCleanup` | Test cleanup cycle logic |\n610: | `TestCleanupController_cleanupResource` | Test single resource cleanup |\n611: | `TestCleanupController_isNamespaceAllowed` | Test namespace filtering |\n612: | `TestCleanupController_DryRun` | Verify dry-run mode |\n613: | `TestCleanupMetrics_RecordCleanup` | Test metrics recording |\n614: \n615: ### Integration Tests\n616: \n617: | Test | Purpose |\n618: |------|---------|\n619: | `TestIntegration_AgentRuntimeCleanup` | Full AgentRuntime cleanup flow |\n620: | `TestIntegration_CodeInterpreterCleanup` | Full CodeInterpreter cleanup flow |\n621: | `TestIntegration_ConcurrentCleanups` | Verify concurrent cleanup limits |\n622: | `TestIntegration_WatchReconnect` | Test watch reconnection on failure |\n623: | `TestIntegration_MetricsExposition` | Verify metrics are exposed correctly |\n624: \n625: ### Test Fixtures\n626: \n627: ```go\n628: func newFakeIdleCleanupController(t *testing.T) (*idleCleanupController, *fake.Clientset) {\n629:     fakeClient := fake.NewSimpleClientset()\n630:     config := DefaultCleanupConfig()\n631:     config.Enabled = true\n632:     config.DryRun = false\n633:     \n634:     tracker := &idleTracker{\n635:         lastActivity: make(map[ResourceKey]time.Time),\n636:         logger:       klog.Background(),\n637:     }\n638:     \n639:     metrics := NewCleanupMetrics(prometheus.NewRegistry())\n640:     \n641:     controller := &idleCleanupController{\n642:         config:       config,\n643:         agentClient:  fakeClient,\n644:         idleTracker:  tracker,\n645:         metrics:      metrics,\n646:         logger:       klog.Background(),\n647:         stopCh:       make(chan struct{}),\n648:     }\n649:     \n650:     return controller, fakeClient\n651: }\n652: \n653: func createTestAgentRuntime(namespace, name string) *runtimev1alpha1.AgentRuntime {\n654:     return &runtimev1alpha1.AgentRuntime{\n655:         ObjectMeta: metav1.ObjectMeta{\n656:             Name:      name,\n657:             Namespace: namespace,\n658:         },\n659:         Status: runtimev1alpha1.AgentRuntimeStatus{\n660:             Phase: runtimev1alpha1.AgentRuntimePhaseRunning,\n661:         },\n662:     }\n663: }\n664: ```\n665: \n666: ---\n667: \n668: ## Acceptance Criteria\n669: \n670: - [ ] `IdleCleanupController` interface implements all required methods\n671: - [ ] `IdleTracker` correctly tracks last activity timestamps\n672: - [ ] Idle detection works with configurable timeouts per resource type\n673: - [ ] Namespace allow/deny lists are respected\n674: - [ ] Dry-run mode logs without deleting\n675: - [ ] Concurrent cleanup limits are enforced\n676: - [ ] Metrics are exposed for monitoring\n677: - [ ] Watch reconnection handles connection failures\n678: - [ ] All unit tests pass\n679: - [ ] Integration tests pass with fake clients\n680: - [ ] Code coverage >= 80%\n681: - [ ] Documentation includes configuration examples\n682: - [ ] Graceful shutdown on controller stop\n683: \n684: ---\n685: \n686: ## Error Handling\n687: \n688: ### CleanupError Types\n689: \n690: ```go\n691: type CleanupErrorType string\n692: \n693: const (\n694:     CleanupErrorNotFound      CleanupErrorType = \"not_found\"\n695:     CleanupErrorPermission    CleanupErrorType = \"permission_denied\"\n696:     CleanupErrorTimeout       CleanupErrorType = \"timeout\"\n697:     CleanupErrorConflict      CleanupErrorType = \"conflict\"\n698:     CleanupErrorUnknown       CleanupErrorType = \"unknown\"\n699: )\n700: \n701: type CleanupError struct {\n702:     Type       CleanupErrorType\n703:     ResourceKind string\n704:     Namespace  string\n705:     Name       string\n706:     Message    string\n707:     Underlying error\n708: }\n709: \n710: func (e *CleanupError) Error() string {\n711:     return fmt.Sprintf(\"cleanup error [%s] for %s/%s/%s: %s\",\n712:         e.Type, e.ResourceKind, e.Namespace, e.Name, e.Message)\n713: }\n714: ```\n715: \n716: ### Error Conditions\n717: \n718: | Condition | Error Type | Handling | Description |\n719: |-----------|------------|----------|-------------|\n720: | Resource already deleted | `CleanupErrorNotFound` | Ignore | Resource was cleaned by another process |\n721: | Permission denied | `CleanupErrorPermission` | Log & retry | Insufficient RBAC permissions |\n722: | Deletion timeout | `CleanupErrorTimeout` | Log & retry | Resource deletion did not complete |\n723: | Finalizer conflict | `CleanupErrorConflict` | Log & skip | Resource has blocking finalizers |\n724: | Unknown API error | `CleanupErrorUnknown` | Log & retry | Uncategorized error |\n725: \n726: ---\n727: \n728: ## Future Considerations\n729: \n730: 1. **Activity Webhooks**: Receive activity notifications from workload manager for precise idle detection\n731: 2. **Graduated Timeouts**: Increase idle timeout for resources that are frequently recreated\n732: 3. **Pre-Cleanup Notification**: Emit events before cleanup for user awareness\n733: 4. **Resource-Specific Policies**: Allow per-resource idle timeout overrides via annotations\n734: 5. **Cluster-Aware Scheduling**: Reduce cleanup frequency during high cluster load\n735: 6. **Audit Logging**: Log all cleanup operations to audit trail\n736: 7. **Custom Resource Conditions**: Add `IdleCleanupCandidate` condition to resources\n737: \n738: ---\n739: \n740: ## References\n741: \n742: - AR-012: Sandbox Infrastructure\n743: - AR-016: PicoD File Management API\n744: - `deployment/client-go.md`: Kubernetes Client-Go Documentation\n745: - `pkg/workloadmanager/reconciler/`: Workload Manager Reconciler\n746: - `pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/types.go`: AgentRuntime and CodeInterpreter Types\n747: - Kubernetes Garbage Collection: https://kubernetes.io/docs/concepts/architecture/garbage-collection/\n\n(End of file - total 747 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# Proposal: Agentd Idle Cleanup Controller (AR-018)\n\n## Summary\n\nImplement an idle cleanup controller in `pkg/agentd` that automatically identifies and terminates idle AgentRuntime and CodeInterpreter resources based on configurable inactivity timeouts, releasing cluster resources and maintaining system hygiene.\n\n---\n\n## Purpose\n\nThe Agentd Idle Cleanup Controller provides:\n\n1. **Resource Reclamation**: Automatically clean up idle agent runtimes and code interpreters to free cluster resources\n2. **Configurable Idle Detection**: Support per-resource-type idle timeout configuration\n3. **Graceful Termination**: Properly finalize resources before deletion with status updates\n4. **Observability**: Emit metrics and logs for cleanup operations\n5. **Safe Operation**: Respect resource11s and avoid cleaning resources with active workloads\n\nThis implementation builds upon the client-go infrastructure from `deployment/client-go.md` and integrates with the workload manager's reconciliation loop to ensure cleaned resources are properly handled.\n","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/changes/AR-018/proposal.md","time":{"start":1775862757885,"end":1775862757918}}}}
