{"type":"text","timestamp":1775862761723,"sessionID":"ses_286553ee8ffe1yJNKlcIkTBKVm","part":{"id":"prt_d79ab4619001YTAGJI3hGw4psH","messageID":"msg_d79ab3a6600185gVFp9VuRKIP2","sessionID":"ses_286553ee8ffe1yJNKlcIkTBKVm","type":"text","text":"Now I have enough context to write the delta-spec.md for AR-018. Let me create it following the OpenSpec format with GIVEN/WHEN/THEN scenarios.","time":{"start":1775862761720,"end":1775862761720}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775862844656,"sessionID":"ses_286553ee8ffe1yJNKlcIkTBKVm","part":{"id":"prt_d79ab48fa0014xGw6zt8BA6tiY","messageID":"msg_d79ab3a6600185gVFp9VuRKIP2","sessionID":"ses_286553ee8ffe1yJNKlcIkTBKVm","type":"tool","tool":"write","callID":"toolu_89961e9e6a414b74b78d2d13","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/pkg/agentd/delta-spec.md","content":"# AR-018 — Agentd Idle Cleanup Controller Delta Specification\n\n## Purpose\n\nDefine the idle cleanup controller implementation for `pkg/agentd` that automatically identifies and terminates idle AgentRuntime and CodeInterpreter resources based on configurable inactivity timeouts, releasing cluster resources and maintaining system hygiene.\n\n## Requirements\n\n### Requirement: IdleCleanupController interface\n\nThe system SHALL define `IdleCleanupController` interface in `pkg/agentd/idle_cleanup.go` with methods `Start(ctx context.Context) error`, `Stop()`, and `CleanupNow(ctx context.Context) (CleanupResult, error)`. `CleanupResult` SHALL include `AgentRuntimesCleaned int`, `CodeInterpretersCleaned int`, and `Errors []CleanupError`.\n\n#### Scenario: Start idle cleanup controller\n\n- **GIVEN** a configured `IdleCleanupController` with `Enabled = true`\n- **WHEN** `Start(ctx)` is called during agentd initialization\n- **THEN** the controller SHALL start periodic cleanup cycles at `CleanupInterval` and watch resource events\n\n#### Scenario: Stop controller gracefully\n\n- **GIVEN** a running `IdleCleanupController`\n- **WHEN** `Stop()` is called during shutdown\n- **THEN** the controller SHALL stop watching resources and complete in-flight cleanup operations\n\n#### Scenario: Trigger immediate cleanup\n\n- **GIVEN** idle resources exist exceeding configured timeouts\n- **WHEN** `CleanupNow(ctx)` is called manually\n- **THEN** an immediate cleanup cycle SHALL run and return `CleanupResult` with counts of cleaned resources\n\n#### Scenario: Controller disabled\n\n- **GIVEN** `CleanupConfig.Enabled = false`\n- **WHEN** `Start(ctx)` is called\n- **THEN** the controller SHALL log \"Idle cleanup controller is disabled\" and return nil without starting watches or cleanup\n\n#### Scenario: CleanupResult with errors\n\n- **GIVEN** cleanup encounters errors during deletion\n- **WHEN** `CleanupNow(ctx)` completes\n- **THEN** `CleanupResult.Errors` SHALL contain `CleanupError` entries for each failed resource\n\n### Requirement: IdleTracker interface\n\nThe system SHALL define `IdleTracker` interface in `pkg/agentd/idle_tracker.go` with methods `UpdateLastActivity(kind, namespace, name string, timestamp time.Time)`, `GetLastActivity(kind, namespace, name string) (time.Time, bool)`, `IsIdle(kind, namespace, name string, timeout time.Duration) bool`, `Remove(kind, namespace, name string)`, and `ListIdleResources(timeout time.Duration) []ResourceKey`. `ResourceKey` SHALL include `Kind`, `Namespace`, and `Name` fields.\n\n#### Scenario: Update last activity timestamp\n\n- **GIVEN** an `IdleTracker` instance\n- **WHEN** `UpdateLastActivity(\"AgentRuntime\", \"default\", \"ar-1\", now)` is called\n- **THEN** the last activity for the resource SHALL be stored and retrievable via `GetLastActivity`\n\n#### Scenario: Check if resource is idle\n\n- **GIVEN** a resource with last activity 35 minutes ago\n- **WHEN** `IsIdle(\"AgentRuntime\", \"default\", \"ar-1\", 30*time.Minute)` is called\n- **THEN** the method SHALL return `true`\n\n#### Scenario: Resource not yet idle\n\n- **GIVEN** a resource with last activity 10 minutes ago\n- **WHEN** `IsIdle(\"AgentRuntime\", \"default\", \"ar-1\", 30*time.Minute)` is called\n- **THEN** the method SHALL return `false`\n\n#### Scenario: No activity recorded\n\n- **GIVEN** a resource never had activity recorded via `UpdateLastActivity`\n- **WHEN** `IsIdle(\"AgentRuntime\", \"default\", \"ar-1\", 30*time.Minute)` is called\n- **THEN** the method SHALL return `true` (treat as idle)\n\n#### Scenario: List all idle resources\n\n- **GIVEN** multiple resources with varying last activity times\n- **WHEN** `ListIdleResources(30*time.Minute)` is called\n- **THEN** only resources idle for >= 30 minutes SHALL be returned\n\n#### Scenario: Remove resource from tracking\n\n- **GIVEN** a tracked resource in `IdleTracker`\n- **WHEN** `Remove(\"AgentRuntime\", \"default\", \"ar-1\")` is called\n- **THEN** the resource SHALL no longer appear in `ListIdleResources` or `GetLastActivity`\n\n#### Scenario: Thread-safe activity updates\n\n- **GIVEN** concurrent calls to `UpdateLastActivity` from multiple goroutines\n- **WHEN** activity updates occur simultaneously\n- **THEN** all updates SHALL be applied correctly without data races\n\n### Requirement: CleanupConfig structure\n\nThe system SHALL define `CleanupConfig` in `pkg/agentd/config.go` with fields `AgentRuntimeIdleTimeout time.Duration`, `CodeInterpreterIdleTimeout time.Duration`, `CleanupInterval time.Duration`, `MaxConcurrentCleanups int`, `Enabled bool`, `DryRun bool`, `NamespaceAllowList []string`, and `NamespaceDenyList []string`. `DefaultCleanupConfig()` SHALL return config with AgentRuntime timeout 30m, CodeInterpreter timeout 15m, interval 5m, max concurrent 10, enabled true.\n\n#### Scenario: Default configuration values\n\n- **GIVEN** `DefaultCleanupConfig()` is called\n- **WHEN** the configuration is inspected\n- **THEN** `AgentRuntimeIdleTimeout` SHALL be `30 * time.Minute`\n\n#### Scenario: Default CodeInterpreter timeout\n\n- **GIVEN** `DefaultCleanupConfig()` is called\n- **WHEN** the configuration is inspected\n- **THEN** `CodeInterpreterIdleTimeout` SHALL be `15 * time.Minute`\n\n#### Scenario: Dry-run mode enabled\n\n- **GIVEN** `CleanupConfig.DryRun = true`\n- **WHEN** cleanup runs\n- **THEN** resources SHALL be logged but not deleted from the API server\n\n#### Scenario: Namespace allow list filtering\n\n- **GIVEN** `NamespaceAllowList = []string{\"default\", \"agents\"}`\n- **WHEN** cleanup evaluates a resource in namespace `\"other\"`\n- **THEN** the resource SHALL NOT be cleaned (namespace not allowed)\n\n#### Scenario: Namespace deny list filtering\n\n- **GIVEN** `NamespaceDenyList = []string{\"kube-system\", \"monitoring\"}`\n- **WHEN** cleanup evaluates a resource in namespace `\"kube-system\"`\n- **THEN** the resource SHALL NOT be cleaned (namespace denied)\n\n#### Scenario: Max concurrent cleanups limit\n\n- **GIVEN** `MaxConcurrentCleanups = 5` and 20 idle resources\n- **WHEN** cleanup cycle runs\n- **THEN** at most 5 deletion operations SHALL execute concurrently\n\n### Requirement: Watch AgentRuntime resources\n\nThe system SHALL implement `watchAgentRuntimes(ctx context.Context)` method that uses `agentClient.RuntimeV1alpha1().AgentRuntimes(metav1.NamespaceAll).Watch()` to monitor resource events. On `Added` or `Modified` events, update idle tracker with `Status.LastActivityTime` or `CreationTimestamp`. On `Deleted` events, remove from tracker.\n\n#### Scenario: Watch receives Added event\n\n- **GIVEN** a new AgentRuntime `\"ar-1\"` is created in namespace `\"default\"`\n- **WHEN** the watch receives the `Added` event\n- **THEN** `IdleTracker.UpdateLastActivity` SHALL be called with the resource's `CreationTimestamp`\n\n#### Scenario: Watch receives Modified event with last activity\n\n- **GIVEN** an existing AgentRuntime with `Status.LastActivityTime` updated\n- **WHEN** the watch receives the `Modified` event\n- **THEN** `IdleTracker.UpdateLastActivity` SHALL be called with `LastActivityTime`\n\n#### Scenario: Watch receives Deleted event\n\n- **GIVEN** an AgentRuntime is deleted from the cluster\n- **WHEN** the watch receives the `Deleted` event\n- **THEN** the resource SHALL be removed from `IdleTracker`\n\n#### Scenario: Watch reconnection on failure\n\n- **GIVEN** the watch connection fails\n- **WHEN** the watch channel closes\n- **THEN** the controller SHALL re-establish the watch with exponential backoff\n\n#### Scenario: Watch context cancellation\n\n- **GIVEN** the context is cancelled during shutdown\n- **WHEN** `ctx.Done()` is signaled\n- **THEN** the watch SHALL stop and call `watcher.Stop()`\n\n### Requirement: Cleanup AgentRuntime resources\n\nThe system SHALL implement `cleanupResource(ctx context.Context, kind, namespace, name string) error` that calls `agentClient.RuntimeV1alpha1().AgentRuntimes(namespace).Delete()` with `GracePeriodSeconds: 30` and `PropagationPolicy: Foreground`. Metrics SHALL be recorded for duration and success/failure.\n\n#### Scenario: Delete idle AgentRuntime\n\n- **GIVEN** an idle AgentRuntime `\"ar-1\"` in namespace `\"default\"`\n- **WHEN** `cleanupResource` is called for this resource\n- **THEN** the AgentRuntime SHALL be deleted from the API server\n\n#### Scenario: Delete with grace period\n\n- **GIVEN** `cleanupResource` is called for an AgentRuntime\n- **WHEN** the delete operation executes\n- **THEN** `GracePeriodSeconds` SHALL be set to 30 seconds\n\n#### Scenario: Foreground propagation policy\n\n- **GIVEN** `cleanupResource` deletes an AgentRuntime\n- **WHEN** the delete options are set\n- **THEN** `PropagationPolicy` SHALL be `DeletePropagationForeground`\n\n#### Scenario: Cleanup non-existent resource\n\n- **GIVEN** an AgentRuntime was already deleted by another process\n- **WHEN** `cleanupResource` attempts deletion\n- **THEN** a `NotFound` error SHALL be handled gracefully (logged, not retried)\n\n#### Scenario: Dry-run skips deletion\n\n- **GIVEN** `CleanupConfig.DryRun = true`\n- **WHEN** `cleanupResource` is called\n- **THEN** the method SHALL log the action but NOT call the delete API\n\n### Requirement: Cleanup CodeInterpreter resources\n\nThe system SHALL implement cleanup for CodeInterpreters using `agentClient.RuntimeV1alpha1().CodeInterpreters(namespace).Delete()` with the same grace period and propagation policy as AgentRuntimes.\n\n#### Scenario: Delete idle CodeInterpreter\n\n- **GIVEN** an idle CodeInterpreter `\"ci-1\"` in namespace `\"default\"`\n- **WHEN** `cleanupResource` is called for this resource\n- **THEN** the CodeInterpreter SHALL be deleted from the API server\n\n#### Scenario: Watch CodeInterpreter events\n\n- **GIVEN** `watchCodeInterpreters(ctx)` is running\n- **WHEN** a CodeInterpreter is created, modified, or deleted\n- **THEN** the `IdleTracker` SHALL be updated accordingly\n\n### Requirement: CleanupMetrics\n\nThe system SHALL define `CleanupMetrics` in `pkg/agentd/cleanup_metrics.go` with Prometheus counters `agentRuntimeCleanupsTotal`, `codeInterpreterCleanupsTotal`, `cleanupErrorsTotal`, histogram `cleanupDurationSeconds`, and gauge `idleResourcesDetected`. Methods SHALL include `RecordCleanup(kind string, duration time.Duration, err error)`, `SetIdleCount(kind string, count int)`, and `RecordError(kind string)`.\n\n#### Scenario: Record successful cleanup\n\n- **GIVEN** an AgentRuntime was successfully cleaned\n- **WHEN** `RecordCleanup(\"AgentRuntime\", 2*time.Second, nil)` is called\n- **THEN** `agentRuntimeCleanupsTotal` counter SHALL increment and duration histogram updated\n\n#### Scenario: Record cleanup error\n\n- **GIVEN** a CodeInterpreter cleanup failed\n- **WHEN** `RecordCleanup(\"CodeInterpreter\", 1*time.Second, err)` is called\n- **THEN** `cleanupErrorsTotal` counter SHALL increment with kind label\n\n#### Scenario: Set idle resource count\n\n- **GIVEN** 15 idle AgentRuntimes detected\n- **WHEN** `SetIdleCount(\"AgentRuntime\", 15)` is called\n- **THEN** `idleResourcesDetected` gauge SHALL be set to 15\n\n#### Scenario: Metrics exposed via Prometheus\n\n- **GIVEN** the metrics registry is registered with Prometheus\n- **WHEN** metrics endpoint is scraped\n- **THEN** all cleanup metrics SHALL be visible with proper labels\n\n### Requirement: Namespace filtering\n\nThe system SHALL implement `isNamespaceAllowed(namespace string) bool` method that checks deny list first, then allow list. System namespaces `kube-system` and `kube-public` SHALL be in the default deny list.\n\n#### Scenario: Deny list takes precedence\n\n- **GIVEN** namespace `\"monitoring\"` is in both allow and deny lists\n- **WHEN** `isNamespaceAllowed(\"monitoring\")` is called\n- **THEN** the method SHALL return `false` (denied)\n\n#### Scenario: Empty allow list allows all\n\n- **GIVEN** `NamespaceAllowList` is empty\n- **WHEN** `isNamespaceAllowed(\"any-namespace\")` is called for a non-denied namespace\n- **THEN** the method SHALL return `true`\n\n#### Scenario: Default system namespace denial\n\n- **GIVEN** default configuration\n- **WHEN** `isNamespaceAllowed(\"kube-system\")` is called\n- **THEN** the method SHALL return `false`\n\n### Requirement: Periodic cleanup cycle\n\nThe system SHALL implement `runCleanup(ctx context.Context)` that runs at `CleanupInterval`, lists idle resources for both types, and cleans allowed namespaces concurrently respecting `MaxConcurrentCleanups`.\n\n#### Scenario: Periodic cleanup execution\n\n- **GIVEN** `CleanupInterval = 5 * time.Minute`\n- **WHEN** the controller is running\n- **THEN** `runCleanup` SHALL be invoked every 5 minutes\n\n#### Scenario: Cleanup both resource types\n\n- **GIVEN** idle AgentRuntimes and CodeInterpreters exist\n- **WHEN** `runCleanup` executes\n- **THEN** both resource types SHALL be processed in the same cycle\n\n#### Scenario: Concurrent cleanup with limit\n\n- **GIVEN** 50 idle resources and `MaxConcurrentCleanups = 10`\n- **WHEN** cleanup runs\n- **THEN** cleanup operations SHALL execute in batches of at most 10 concurrent deletions\n\n#### Scenario: Cleanup cycle logs summary\n\n- **GIVEN** cleanup cycle completes\n- **WHEN** all operations finish\n- **THEN** a log message SHALL indicate number of resources cleaned and any errors\n\n### Requirement: Environment variable configuration\n\nThe system SHALL support configuration via environment variables: `AGENTD_CLEANUP_ENABLED`, `AGENTD_CLEANUP_DRY_RUN`, `AGENTD_AGENT_RUNTIME_IDLE_TIMEOUT`, `AGENTD_CODE_INTERPRETER_IDLE_TIMEOUT`, `AGENTD_CLEANUP_INTERVAL`, `AGENTD_MAX_CONCURRENT_CLEANUPS`, `AGENTD_CLEANUP_NAMESPACE_ALLOW_LIST`, `AGENTD_CLEANUP_NAMESPACE_DENY_LIST`.\n\n#### Scenario: Load cleanup enabled from env\n\n- **GIVEN** `AGENTD_CLEANUP_ENABLED=false` is set\n- **WHEN** configuration is loaded\n- **THEN** `CleanupConfig.Enabled` SHALL be `false`\n\n#### Scenario: Load idle timeout from env\n\n- **GIVEN** `AGENTD_AGENT_RUNTIME_IDLE_TIMEOUT=1h` is set\n- **WHEN** configuration is loaded\n- **THEN** `AgentRuntimeIdleTimeout` SHALL be `1 * time.Hour`\n\n#### Scenario: Load namespace allow list from env\n\n- **GIVEN** `AGENTD_CLEANUP_NAMESPACE_ALLOW_LIST=\"default,agents\"` is set\n- **WHEN** configuration is loaded\n- **THEN** `NamespaceAllowList` SHALL be `[]string{\"default\", \"agents\"}`\n\n#### Scenario: Invalid duration falls back to default\n\n- **GIVEN** `AGENTD_CLEANUP_INTERVAL=invalid` is set\n- **WHEN** configuration is loaded\n- **THEN** the default interval SHALL be used and a warning logged\n\n### Requirement: CleanupError types\n\nThe system SHALL define `CleanupError` struct with fields `Type CleanupErrorType`, `ResourceKind string`, `Namespace string`, `Name string`, `Message string`, and `Underlying error`. Error types SHALL include `CleanupErrorNotFound`, `CleanupErrorPermission`, `CleanupErrorTimeout`, `CleanupErrorConflict`, and `CleanupErrorUnknown`.\n\n#### Scenario: NotFound error handling\n\n- **GIVEN** resource is already deleted when cleanup attempts\n- **WHEN** API returns NotFound error\n- **THEN** `CleanupError.Type` SHALL be `CleanupErrorNotFound` and error is ignored\n\n#### Scenario: Permission denied error\n\n- **GIVEN** RBAC does not allow delete on resource\n- **WHEN** cleanup attempts deletion\n- **THEN** `CleanupError.Type` SHALL be `CleanupErrorPermission` and logged for review\n\n#### Scenario: Error string formatting\n\n- **GIVEN** a `CleanupError` with kind=\"AgentRuntime\", namespace=\"default\", name=\"ar-1\"\n- **WHEN** `Error()` is called\n- **THEN** the string SHALL include resource identification and error message\n\n### Requirement: Graceful shutdown\n\nThe system SHALL implement graceful shutdown in `Stop()` that closes `stopCh`, waits for in-flight cleanups via `sync.WaitGroup`, and logs shutdown completion.\n\n#### Scenario: Stop closes stop channel\n\n- **GIVEN** a running controller\n- **WHEN** `Stop()` is called\n- **THEN** `stopCh` SHALL be closed signaling goroutines to exit\n\n#### Scenario: Wait for goroutines to finish\n\n- **GIVEN** cleanup goroutines are running\n- **WHEN** `Stop()` is called\n- **THEN** the method SHALL block until all goroutines complete via `wg.Wait()`\n\n#### Scenario: Shutdown logging\n\n- **GIVEN** controller shutdown completes\n- **WHEN** all goroutines exit\n- **THEN** a log message SHALL indicate \"Idle cleanup controller stopped\"\n\n### Requirement: Integration with client-go\n\nThe system SHALL use generated client-go from `deployment/client-go.md` including `versioned.Interface` for typed client access, `RuntimeV1alpha1Interface` for resource operations, and `watch.Interface` for event streaming.\n\n#### Scenario: Create typed client for AgentRuntimes\n\n- **GIVEN** a configured `versioned.Interface` client\n- **WHEN** `client.RuntimeV1alpha1().AgentRuntimes(\"default\")` is called\n- **THEN** a typed `AgentRuntimeInterface` SHALL be returned for CRUD operations\n\n#### Scenario: Watch with typed client\n\n- **GIVEN** a typed `AgentRuntimeInterface`\n- **WHEN** `Watch(ctx, metav1.ListOptions{})` is called\n- **THEN** a `watch.Interface` SHALL stream `Added`, `Modified`, `Deleted` events\n\n#### Scenario: List idle resources with label selector\n\n- **GIVEN** resources with various labels\n- **WHEN** `List(ctx, metav1.ListOptions{LabelSelector: \"app=test\"})` is called\n- **THEN** only matching resources SHALL be returned for idle evaluation\n\n## Dependencies\n\n| Dependency | Source | Usage |\n|------------|--------|-------|\n| `k8s.io/client-go` | External | Kubernetes client interfaces |\n| `github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/client-go` | Generated | Typed client for runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh |\n| `github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1` | Generated | AgentRuntime and CodeInterpreter types |\n| `k8s.io/apimachinery/pkg/watch` | External | Watch event streaming |\n| `k8s.io/apimachinery/pkg/apis/meta/v1` | External | Metadata, deletion options |\n| `k8s.io/klog/v2` | External | Structured logging |\n| `prometheus/client_golang/prometheus` | External | Metrics exposition |\n| `golang.org/x/sync/errgroup` | External | Concurrent cleanup with limits |\n\n## Files to Create/Modify\n\n| File | Action | Description |\n|------|--------|-------------|\n| `pkg/agentd/idle_cleanup.go` | Create | IdleCleanupController interface and implementation |\n| `pkg/agentd/idle_tracker.go` | Create | IdleTracker interface and implementation |\n| `pkg/agentd/config.go` | Create | CleanupConfig structure and loading |\n| `pkg/agentd/cleanup_metrics.go` | Create | Prometheus metrics for cleanup |\n| `pkg/agentd/idle_cleanup_test.go` | Create | Unit tests for cleanup controller |\n| `pkg/agentd/idle_tracker_test.go` | Create | Unit tests for idle detection |\n| `pkg/agentd/config_test.go` | Create | Unit tests for configuration |\n| `pkg/agentd/cleanup_metrics_test.go` | Create | Unit tests for metrics |\n\n## Testing Strategy\n\n1. **Unit Tests**: Mock client-go interfaces, test idle detection logic, verify namespace filtering\n2. **Integration Tests**: Use fake clientset from `client-go/clientset/versioned/fake/`, test full cleanup flows\n3. **Concurrent Tests**: Verify thread-safety of IdleTracker under concurrent access\n4. **Error Injection Tests**: Use reactors on fake client to test error handling paths\n"},"output":"Wrote file successfully.","metadata":{"diagnostics":{},"filepath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/pkg/agentd/delta-spec.md","exists":false,"truncated":false},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/pkg/agentd/delta-spec.md","time":{"start":1775862844640,"end":1775862844652}}}}
